definitions.definition: ( countable , uncountable ) Any coniferous tree of the genus Pinus .
examples: The northern slopes were covered mainly in pine .

definitions.definition: ( countable ) Any tree (usually coniferous) which resembles a member of this genus in some respect.
( uncountable ) The wood of this tree.
( archaic except Caribbean , Guyana , South Africa , Australia ) A pineapple .
( sports , uncountable , colloquial ) The bench , where players sit when not playing.
( uncountable , colloquial ) A counter or bartop .
examples: I'll be behind the pine slinging your favorite cold ones, so come and see me!
